import React from "react"; import "./ControlPins.css"; class ReadValue extends React.Component { constructor(props) { super(props); this.state = { readValue: { PD4: "", PD5: "", PD6: "", PA1: "", PA2: "", PA3: "", PD3: "", PD2: "", PD1: "", PC7: "", PC6: "", PC5: "", PC4: "", PC3: "", PB4: "", PB5: "", }, }; } componentWillUnmount() { clearInterval(this.intervalID); } async componentDidMount() { console.log(this.state.readValue.PD4) try { this.intervalID = setInterval(async () => { const res = await fetch("http://192.168.0.111:8082/get-values"); const pinValues = await res.json(); // console.log(pinValues); this.setState( { readValue: pinValues, }, () => { this.props.getReadValCallback(this.state.readValue); console.log("In ReadValue "); console.log(this.state.readValue); } ); }, 3000); } catch (e) { console.log(e); } } render() { return (
); } } export default ReadValue;
